author: AceShowbiz.com
title: Kaley Cuoco Cannels Jedi at Horse Riding Competition
text:
Comments The 'Big Bang Theory' actress has a Lightsaber showdown with Darth Vader at the charity event in Los Angeles. 
Kaley Cuoco went full Jedi at the Longines Masters of Los Angeles. " The Big Bang Theory " actress was decked out in a tan tunic and a pair of matching trousers complete with a utility belt. On top of that, she wielded her own Lightsaber at the Saturday, October 3 charity event. She was joined by other crew who dressed up in "Star Wars" characters like Princess Leia, Darth Vader, Stormtrooper, and Chewbacca. "Had an amazing night with my Star Wars team at the @mastersgrandslam charity class benefitting #rideon !!!" she wrote on Instagram. A photo posted by @normancook on Oct 4, 2015 at 12:25am PDT At one point, the newly-single actress even hit the center field and battled the Darth Vader. "@normancook battles the dark side in the competition arena! #LiveMasters," the event's organizers wrote a caption for an IG picture of the Lightsaber showdown. A photo posted by @normancook on Oct 4, 2015 at 7:15am PDT A photo posted by Longines Masters (@mastersgrandslam) on Oct 3, 2015 at 10:48pm PDT Cuoco was also there to take part in the horse riding competition. After attending an opening gala on Thursday, she competed on the following day and won. "2nd place in the 1.30 GP," she proudly informed her online followers. "@normancook basks in her Pro-Am Style & Competition win for @rideontherapy at @Longines Masters of Los Angeles," the organizers said in another picture.
